<h3>What?&nbsp;&nbsp;</h3>
<p>OECD- Inclusive growth is economic growth that is distributed fairly across society and creates opportunities for all.</p>
<p>CLOUD&nbsp; =ASPECTS of inclusive growth</p>
<ol>
<li>SOCIAL =&nbsp; poverty reduce + equality of opportunity promote + access to essential services.</li>
<li>ECONOMIC = ES2017 - 30% youth in NEET.</li>
<li>TECHNOLOGY</li>
<li>Financial inclusion = <span style="color:#2ecc71">RBI - financial inclusion index</span>&nbsp;Access, Usage and Quality are the 3 parameters which will have total 97 indicators.</li>
<li>SKILL = Employment create&nbsp; +</li></ol>
<h3>India has inclusive growth? - NO</h3>
<ol>
<li>Gender = Eco + Political Gender gap (132/150 GGI of WEF)</li>
<li>Informalisation of workforce (26% 2005 to 36% 2015)</li>
<li>GINI coefficient rise + JOBLESS growth&nbsp;</li>
<li>INEQUALITY = oxfam</li>
<li>Highest Illiterates in the world.</li></ol>
<h3>India has inclusive growth? - YES</h3>
<ol>
<li>Largest reduction in poverty in 1990-2005 decade (8% decrease, 36-&gt;28)</li>
<li>IMR MMR reduce</li>
<li>Life expectancy rose.</li></ol>
<h3>Challenges to inclusive growth&nbsp;</h3>
<ol>
<li>poverty = MPI 2018 (271 mn lifted out of poverty between 2005-2015)<br />
-&gt; Vulnerability to MPI = 19% population, extreme MPI&nbsp; = 8%</li>
<li>unemployment = Number + Quality&nbsp;</li>
<li>Social = regional, gender, caste disparities + public expenditure on health edu low + malnutrition high (102 in GHI)&nbsp;</li></ol>
<h3>Way forward&nbsp;</h3>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<ol>
<li>IDI by WEF = least inclusive among G-20&nbsp;</li>
<li>measure of inequality based on three parameters: :
<ol>
<li>Growth and development</li>
<li>Inclusion</li>
<li>Inter-generational equity and sustainability.</li></ol></li></ol>
